{
  "texts": [
    "Similarly, RHA exhibits a fineness level akin to SF and MK, providing comparable performance benefits.",
    "In contrast, ESP shows the lowest fineness among the materials examined, functioning mainly as a filler.",
    "While ESP aids in stabilizing the concrete mix, its impact on strength and durability is modest.",
    "FA also has a relatively low fineness, leading to a slower improvement in mechanical properties.To address the limitations of lower fineness, several strategies can be applied.",
    "Pre-grinding or milling can enhance particle surface area, thereby increasing reactivity and pore-filling potential."
  ]
}